  "text": "The C 60 crystal motivates further theoretical characterizations because there is experimental data on structure [CITATION_1] . We note that while our unconstrained relaxation (modeling a primitive cell) predicts a triclinic structure, the actual structure deviation is small (see Table  A1 ). This difference is, in fact, expected. The ground state should have two different alignments of the symmetry axis relative to the crystal directions [CITATION_2] . In choosing a primitive modeling, we are, on principle grounds, prevented from fully representing the actual C 60 crystal ground state.",
